did.abstract: Collection includes Cherry Tree yearbooks, photographs from the Cherry Tree of buildings, students groups, events, clubs, departments, presidents, etc.

prefercite.head: Preferred citation
prefercite.p: Cherry Tree Yearbook records, University Archives, Special Collections Research Center, The George Washington University.

accessrestrict.head: Restrictions on Access
accessrestrict.p: Collection is open for use, with the exception of the series of yearbooks. Researchers are directed to use the copies located in the Special Collections reading room instead.

acqinfo.head: Acquisition Information
acqinfo.p: Materials acquired through transfers from Cherry Tree Office.

userestrict.head: Restrictions on Use
userestrict.p: Some material may be copyrighted or restricted. It is the patron's obligation to determine and satisfy copyright or other case restrictions when publishing or otherwise distributing materials found in the collections.

bioghist.head: Historical or Biographical Note
bioghist.p: Originally called The Columbiad in 1890, the yearbook became The C in 1904, The Mall in 1905, and finally the Cherry Tree in 1908.

scopecontent.head: Collection Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: This collection consists primarily of photographs from the Cherry Tree of buildings, students groups, events, clubs, departments, presidents, etc. It also includes a set of extra copies of the yearbook which may be deaccessioned as needed.

arrangement.head: Collection Organization
arrangement.p: Organized into 10 series: one series of yearbooks, one of office files, and eight series of photogoraphs

altformavail.head: Existence and Location of Copies
altformavail.p: Two copies of the Cherry Tree Yearbook and its predecessors are cataloged in the main library catalog under LD 1947.C5. One of these copies is located in the Special Collections reading room, and the other is stored in the Special Collections' closed stacks area.
The yearbooks have been digitized and are available online at the Internet Archive.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series contains correspondence, a poster, a postcard, a list and forms. They range in date from 1939 to 2000. The materials concern ordering yearbooks, taking pictures, information to accompany pictures, and requiting new employees.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Photos and negatives for 1993-1994 yearbook - concerts, athletics, students, aids quilt, sororities/fraternaties, cheerleaders, GW mascot, black people's union, buildings, campus scenes, theater, engineers egg drop, events, faculty/staff, fall festival/spring fling, greek life, homecoming, honors program, international week, President Trachtenberg, President Elliott, President Bush, President Gorbachev, Vaclav Havel, Shimon Perez, speakers, student association, chalk-in, troubadours, etc.
